erofrm6.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=1708.topic&index=4>Reply</a>   <BR><img src=http://members.cox.net/jessamyn5/JessSm.jpg height=107 width=140 ></td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: smithing woes</span><hr size=1> Because some of the higher end smiths do not need skillups. For example, a smith with 242 skill and a Geerlok effectively has their skill MAXXED. You would be paying for the better chances to make with the materials provided. You could always go to a lower skill smith who does free combines, and have you go through 3-4x the number of materials.<br>
<br>
In that case the person is paying for the time and skill of the smith. If you disagree with it, wait till other smiths sell the sickles at 2k each and buy one that way. *shrug* <p><p align="center">
