</p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#383838><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub42.ezboard.com/ujessamynsunweaver.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Jessamyn Sunweaver</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Veteran</span><br> <font color=#ff0000>(7/19/02 5:40:15 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub42.ezboard.com/fayonaerofrm6.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=1708.topic&index=5>Reply</a>   <BR><img src=http://members.cox.net/jessamyn5/JessSm.jpg height=107 width=140 ></td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: smithing woes</span><hr size=1> Another reason for fees. Not everyone in this world is nice and honest. Would be wonderful for everyone who is, but this is not the case. <br>
<br>
If you shout &quot;Free combines!&quot; all the unhonest ones will come out of the woodword with the components, and then want 5 others to sell for profit. <br>
<br>
You want to sell items for profit? Fine, but them for 2k then try and sell them for 2.5k. We worked for our skill. We are not a living commonmart to gyp. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#383838><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub42.ezboard.com/utheperfectflaw.showPublicProfile?language=EN>ThePerfectFlaw</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Druidhugger</span><br> <font color=#ff0000>(7/19/02 6:07:42 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub42.ezboard.com/fayonaerofrm6.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=1708.topic&index=6>Reply</a>   <BR><img src=http://perfectflaw.wox.org/images/jolly.gif WIDTH=60 HEIGHT=60></td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: smithing woes</span><hr size=1> /em looks around for his violin.<br>
<br>
Knew I left it around here somewhere.  It's the worlds smallest. <p><a href=http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=35824><img src=http://perfectflaw.wox.org/images/sinfest/selfish.gif></a><br>
</p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#383838><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub42.ezboard.com/uoranabumthumper.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Orana Bumthumper</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Settler</span><br> <font color=#ff0000>(7/19/02 6:17:21 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub42.ezboard.com/fayonaerofrm6.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=1708.topic&index=7>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: smithing woes</span><hr size=1> I have always been under the assumption that it would be EITHER a fee for the combines OR one set of materials for a 2ns combine.  To ask for both does seem to be a bit much.  I will admit, Im no master smith so I have no real clue as to the cash involved with getting that far up the smithing ladder.<br>
<br>
But to be honest...most smiths I have hired either ask me for a fee or 2 sets of materials.  What would you have done if you had failed on BOTH attamepts?<br>
<br>
 <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#383838><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub42.ezboard.com/upalarran.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Palarran</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Local Resident</span><br> <font color=#ff0000>(7/19/02 7:23:28 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub42.ezboard.com/fayonaerofrm6.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=1708.topic&index=8>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: smithing woes</span><hr size=1> The 2 sets of materials really works better with items that are valuable but relatively easy for the tradeskiller to combine.  After all, to profit the tradeskiller needs a reasonable chance of succeeding twice in a row.<br>
The maximum success rate on sickles is somewhere around 50%.  This means that if provided two sets of materials in exchange for the first success, the tradeskiller only has a 25% chance of making any kind of profit for their time.  Sometimes a 25% chance of making an extra is enough payment to convince a tradeskiller to help someone out, and sometimes it isn't.<br>
<br>
If Muffildy had failed both, the way I understand it she would not have asked for a fee as the 500pp was to be paid upon success.  It was not a fee for making the combine regardless of outcome. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#383838><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub42.ezboard.com/uliper.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Liper</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Wanderer</span><br> <font color=#ff0000>(7/19/02 7:51:02 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub42.ezboard.com/fayonaerofrm6.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=1708.topic&index=9>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: smithing woes</span><hr size=1> Thing was I was paying 500pp for the attempt not outcome. She agreed to do it for 300pp, she wanted me out of her hair.<br>
<br>
when I asked her if she succeds on both attempts do I get both?  She said no, I asked why, she said because you didn't met my original asking price.  So I met the original asking price.<br>
<br>
Don't you think I should of gotten both and handed her 500?  <br>
 <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#383838><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub42.ezboard.com/uliper.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Liper</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Wanderer</span><br> <font color=#ff0000>(7/19/02 7:54:45 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub42.ezboard.com/fayonaerofrm6.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=1708.topic&index=10>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: smithing woes</span><hr size=1> the other reason that i didnt mention is its a charge on success<br>
<br>
Well if you didn't mention it how am I to know?  If you mention it after both combines are made, doesn't it make you look a bit shady?<br>
<br>
Also it's not like wasn't bieng nice and giving you extra tempers and what nots. (admitidly they are cheap, just takes putting in boxes and hitting combine)<br>
<br>
I am sorry you were to distracted with playing NWN (as you told a friend of mine who was talking with you) to tell me how you wanted things.   <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#383838><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub42.ezboard.com/ujessamynsunweaver.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Jessamyn Sunweaver</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Veteran</span><br> <font color=#ff0000>(7/19/02 8:14:55 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub42.ezboard.com/fayonaerofrm6.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=1708.topic&index=11>Reply</a>   <BR><img src=http://members.cox.net/jessamyn5/JessSm.jpg height=107 width=140 ></td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: smithing woes</span><hr size=1> Because it doesn't make sense that &quot;Sure, you give me 500pp and you get every sickle I manage to make&quot;.<br>
<br>
Now, it leaves to common sense that she meant she would charge 500pp on SUCCESS or PER ATTEMPT. <br>
<br>
Now, if you only had the 300p when you said you had 500, it means you would only get 1 sickle. 500p plus stuff needed to make the 1 sickle seemed like the original agreement. <br>
<br>
So you know what it means if you want 2 sickles? Another 500p for the second one. <br>
<br>
Makes sense.<br>
<br>
She did offer you the components back for the second one after all, plus the first sickle for the 500p.<br>
<br>
So in all honestly, she seems to of held her end of the deal. You suddenly decided not to hold yours.<br>
<br>
Nuff Said <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#383838><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub42.ezboard.com/ujessamynsunweaver.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Jessamyn Sunweaver</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Veteran</span><br> <font color=#ff0000>(7/19/02 8:19:10 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub42.ezboard.com/fayonaerofrm6.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=1708.topic&index=12>Reply</a>   <BR><img src=http://members.cox.net/jessamyn5/JessSm.jpg height=107 width=140 ></td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: smithing woes</span><hr size=1> I personally know Muff is a good person and would not rip anyone off. <br>
<br>
Yes, there may of been a miscommunication or misunderstanding, it happens alot.<br>
<br>
It seems that she DID attempt to fix it by offering the second set of components back and the first sickle for 500p (or 300p as the second agreement went since he &quot;suddenly&quot; realized he didn't have 500, AS AGREED). <br>
<br>
This just makes this so-called Lipper person look VERY bad, at least in my opinion. And spending time in Bazaar in attempt to tarnish Muff's name makes it even worse.<br>
<br>
